K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraAniynu","text_ar":"عَرَانِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo $um~u AlEaraAniyni","text_ar":"هُمْ شُمُّ العَرَانِينِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are high in respect of the noses,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the bridges thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"often meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they are haughty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disdainful"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, Msb.) And one of the learned has used it metaphorically, saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waA^aSobaHa Ald~ahoru *uw AlEironiyni qado judiEaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And nosed fortune became mutilated in the nose;"},{"kind":"text","text":"by"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nosed"},{"kind":"text","text":"being app. meant (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"haughty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disdainful;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and by"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mutilated in the nose,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"marred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abased"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) Hence also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraAniynu Als~aHaAbi","text_ar":"عَرَانِينُ السَّحَابِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The first of the rains of the clouds."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A noble chief:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraAniynu","text_ar":"عَرَانِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chiefs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) of a people, or party, (S,) or of the people, or of men. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","TA","K"]}]}}